Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}(drizzle), season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.
> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

Halve the @burger buns{2}.

Put the @cider vinegar{15%milliliter} in a #medium bowl{} with the @sugar{½%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then mix together.

Add the tomatoes to the dressing and mix again, then set aside.

When the wedges have about 12 mins remaining, place the @unconventional plant-based burgers{2} on a lightly oiled large baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until browned, ~{8-9%minutes}.

Once the burgers are cooked, remove from the oven and place the cheese on top of them. Put the burger buns on the same #baking tray{}.

Return to the middle shelf of your oven until the cheese is melted and the buns are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the bun bases (see pantry for amount) and the @onion marmalade{30%grams} on the bun lids. Top the bases with the cheesy plant-based burger and a handful of @wild rocket{40%grams}, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Add the remaining rocket to the #bowl{} of tomatoes and toss to coat in the dressing.

Serve your burgers with the wedges and salad alongside.

Enjoy!